                <h1>The Yellow Wallpaper: A Haunting Short Film Exploration</h1>
                <p>The short film "The Yellow Wallpaper," based on Charlotte Perkins Gilman's iconic story, delves into the psychological struggles of a woman confined to a room. Through haunting visuals and an evocative score, it explores themes of mental illness, isolation, and the quest for identity, ultimately revealing the profound impact of repression on the human psyche.</p>
